<br>
With that said, Taranna, you asked Somthor to consider a situation where one of his relatives might be put on death row thought innocent.<br>
<br>
I ask you to consider a situation where a family member of yours is raped and murdered, and the criminal who did so spends 10... maybe 15 years in a state prison watching cable TV, enjoying internet access and earning his college equivalency degree on your dime.<br>
<br>
Crimes don't just fall down on their criminals like they do their victims. People aren't raped according to stastics. Others aren't murdered by thin air. There is a criminal who chooses to act in the way he does, and we must hold them accountable for such action. If our government cannot protect us from the use of force, be it from at home or abroad, it must change to do so - or be invalid. <br>
<br>
&quot;Criminal rights&quot; is a contradiction of terms. A criminal is someone who has actively sought to destroy the society which would otherwise act to protect them. A true criminal forfeits their rights by their actions; they impose physical force upon someone else, and in doing so show their disrespect for rights. Everything they are granted afterwards is on our good graces as the violated party.<br>
<br>
Do not paint these people out to be violated saints.<br>
<br>
Now for obvious reasons, it benefits society to have a justice system that is driven by reason without malice. It benefits society to be just and fair, and for our system to engage in due process to apply justice accurately. This is as much for the innocent as it is for the guilty.<br>
<br>
-Junk <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bascension10244.showUserPublicProfile?gid=konjunktion>Konjunktion</A> at: 11/20/03 11:00 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bascension10244.showUserPublicProfile?gid=istaril>Istaril</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(11/20/03 12:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://p075.ezboard.com/fascension10244frm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=428.topic&index=32>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> There are tons of points that have and will be brought up. The fact that countries with death penatly have more crime, the fact that death penalty is irreversible, the fact that... the list goes on. <br>
<br>
Essentially though, to me, death penalty is wrong. It's the eye for an eye filosophy that I find unnaceptable. Someone kills someone, so you kill him. Are you not stooping to his level? Shouldn't someone then kill you? And someone kill him because he killed you?<br>
